---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Best for US Expats', href: '/best/us-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Germany Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/germany/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', geoblue: true, allianz: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', geoblue: true, allianz: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', geoblue: 'Good', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', geoblue: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Dental', geoblue: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', geoblue: 'Integrated (BCBS)', allianz: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'US Network', geoblue: 'BCBS (90%+ US hospitals)', allianz: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', geoblue: true, allianz: true },
  { feature: 'Annual Maximum', geoblue: '$1M-$5M', allianz: '€1M-Unlimited' },
  { feature: 'Plan Flexibility', geoblue: 'Moderate', allianz: 'High (modular)' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', geoblue: '$150-220/mo', allianz: '€100-140/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', geoblue: '$280-380/mo', allianz: '€170-230/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', geoblue: '$300-440/mo', allianz: '€200-280/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', geoblue: '$500-750/mo', allianz: '€350-480/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue vs Allianz Care"
  description="Compare GeoBlue and Allianz Care. US-focused BCBS network vs flexible European insurer for international health coverage."
  headline="GeoBlue vs Allianz Care: US Network vs European Flexibility"
  subheadline="Two different approaches to international coverage. Here's how to choose based on your needs."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/compare/geoblue-vs-allianz-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue and Allianz Care represent two distinct philosophies in international health insurance. GeoBlue is built around seamless US coverage through the Blue Cross Blue Shield network—ideal for Americans abroad. Allianz Care offers modular, flexible plans popular with European expats and those who want to customize their coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">GeoBlue</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>BCBS network access in the US</li>
        <li>Built for American expats</li>
        <li>90%+ US hospital coverage</li>
        <li>Strong emergency support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Allianz Care</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Modular plan design</li>
        <li>Strong European networks</li>
        <li>Competitive pricing</li>
        <li>Flexible coverage options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from GeoBlue and Allianz Care for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The core medical coverage is comparable, but the US integration and plan flexibility differ significantly.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US network:</strong> GeoBlue's BCBS network covers 90%+ of US hospitals with direct billing. Allianz treats US coverage as an add-on with limited network access</li>
    <li><strong>Plan flexibility:</strong> Allianz offers modular plans where you choose your coverage components. GeoBlue has more fixed plan structures</li>
    <li><strong>Geographic focus:</strong> GeoBlue is optimized for Americans; Allianz works well globally but excels in Europe</li>
    <li><strong>Maximum limits:</strong> Allianz offers unlimited coverage options; GeoBlue caps at $5M (still substantial)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care is generally 25-35% less expensive than GeoBlue, reflecting different market positioning and the value of US network access.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>GeoBlue's premium includes valuable BCBS network access</li>
    <li>Allianz's modular approach lets you reduce costs by dropping unnecessary coverage</li>
    <li>Adding US coverage to Allianz narrows the price gap significantly</li>
    <li>Both offer deductible options to manage premiums</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="Prices vary by age, location, and coverage choices."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>GeoBlue</strong> leverages the Blue Cross Blue Shield network—the largest in the US—plus international partnerships. This means seamless care whether you're in the US or abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> has strong networks in Europe and growing partnerships globally. Their European coverage is particularly robust, with extensive direct-billing arrangements.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer online claims submission and mobile apps. GeoBlue's US claims are often automatic through BCBS. Allianz processes claims efficiently but may require more manual submission internationally.
  </p>

  <h3>For Different Expat Types</h3>
  <p>
    American expats who visit home regularly will find GeoBlue's network access invaluable. Expats based in Europe or those who don't need US coverage can save significantly with Allianz.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose GeoBlue If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're an American expat</li>
        <li>You return to the US regularly</li>
        <li>BCBS network access matters to you</li>
        <li>You want seamless US/international coverage</li>
        <li>You have US doctors you want to keep seeing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Budget is a priority</li>
        <li>You're based in Europe</li>
        <li>You don't need US coverage</li>
        <li>You want to customize your plan</li>
        <li>You prefer modular coverage options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This comparison largely comes down to your relationship with the US healthcare system.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>GeoBlue</strong> is the clear choice for American expats who maintain ties to home. The BCBS network access is genuinely valuable—90%+ of US hospitals with direct billing makes stateside care effortless. You pay more, but the convenience is real.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> makes more sense if US coverage isn't a priority. The modular plan design, competitive pricing, and strong European networks serve expats well. You can always add US coverage if needed, though it won't match GeoBlue's network.
  </p>
  <p>
    Get quotes from both—if you don't need US coverage, Allianz could save you 25-35%. If you do, GeoBlue's premium is likely worth it.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
